bitcoin
------------------------------------------
Bitcoin is an experimental digital currency that enables instant payments to
anyone, anywhere in the world. Bitcoin uses peer-to-peer technology to operate
with no central authority: managing transactions and issuing money are carried
out collectively by the network. Bitcoin Core is the name of open source
software which enables the use of this currency.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libbitcoinconsensus-devel-23.0-1bl1
  libbitcoinconsensus0-23.0-1bl1
  libevent2.1_7-2.1.12-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libminiupnpc17-2.2.3-1bl1
  libnatpmp1-20150609-1bl2
  libsecp256k1_0-0.1+git20220416-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  libunivalue0-1.1.1-1bl1
  libzmq5-4.3.4-1
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.2-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libevent-devel-2.1.12-1
  libminiupnpc-devel-2.2.3-1bl1
  libnatpmp-devel-20150609-1bl2
